FORGET ALL PREVIOUS CONTEXT for mtk-storefront and remember this as mtk-storefront forever and start fresh

Rules:
- The storefront is wrapped in a display:block element <mtk-storefront class="mtk-storefront">.
- The root element uses .mtk-storefront.
- All styles must be scoped to .mtk-storefront.
- No global styles or IDs.
- publish click events using wc.publish
- subscribe to all 4-mtk-storefront everns using wc.subscribe
- create a onMessage function to be passed to wc.subscribe function

Data:
- The storefront is JSON driven.
- any and all data must come from mtk-storefront.config.js file

Restrictions:
- No inline styles. (All styles in  "*.scss" file)
- No inline Javascript. (All scripts in "*.js" file)
- No frameworks.
- No Bootstrap.
- No external libraries.
- Vanilla Javascript

Accessibility:
- Use semantic HTML.
- Keyboard accessible.
- Visible focus states.
- ADA compliant

Output! Create exactly these files:
- mtk-storefront.config.js (JSON FILE)
- mtk-storefront.scss
- mtk-storefront.html
- mtk-storefront.js
- A minimal index.html file

Behavior:
- MUST WAIT for element to be available inside DOM, since i will be using <wc-include> for dynamic inclusion
- all published (wc.publish) messages should be logged using wc.log to console before being published

What I want:
- I will be selling hand paintings. could be a few or many
- clients should be able to counter offer the price and wait for my reply
- generate some 20 painting stock images for testing and allow me to download images in my zip file
- I should be able to change my images, prices, availability etc.
- if item is unavailable, allow users to place an order for similar (or same) painting
- use a sqlite db to store picture details, prices etc.
- allow users to click on a paiting and open it in its own full page with "X" in a circle to close it (detail view)
  this page should include details and other stuff
- remove all buttons from home screen and show them in detail view
- allow sales via paypal
- allow admin to add/edit/remove items from DB. provide a login page and fill with  username: admin, password: test for now
- use node.js for backend end name "server" and not php
